OL,4,Cunpredictable weather
OL,6,FBritish potatoes are usually available
OL,7,Ffor people to buy all year round but
OL,8,Frecently supermarkets have had to
OL,9,Fimport spuds to keep shelves stocked.
OL,11,FMeanwhile, Chorley livestock farmer
OL,12,FHelen Drinkhall says she "loses sleep"
OL,13,Fover the relentless rain which she
OL,14,Fsays will have a knock-on effect later
OL,15,Fon in the year.
OL,17,FShe explains: "We're making the food
OL,18,Ffor winter now and the grass is ready
OL,19,Fto be cut, so we could really do with
OL,20,Fgetting it bailed and stored.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/7
